{
  "page": "Crownlands men",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Franz_Miklis_KingswoodFiefdom.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e9/Franz_Miklis_KingswoodFiefdom.jpg/350px-Franz_Miklis_KingswoodFiefdom.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"266\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e9/Franz_Miklis_KingswoodFiefdom.jpg/525px-Franz_Miklis_KingswoodFiefdom.jpg 1.5x, /images/e/e9/Franz_Miklis_KingswoodFiefdom.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Franz_Miklis_KingswoodFiefdom.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood\" title=\"Kingswood\">Kingswood</a> fiefdom, by Franz Miklis © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Crownlands men</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> are natives of the <a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">crownlands</a>, an eastern region of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. Sworn directly to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> the crownlands were created in the aftermath of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Ethnicity\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ethnicity</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ethnicity\">Ethnicity</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Crownlands_men&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Ethnicity\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>What is now the <a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">crownlands</a> was settled in antiquity by <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>, with <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a> then conquering southern <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> during their <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_the_Andals\" title=\"Coming of the Andals\">migration to Westeros</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_arrival_of_the_andals.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_arrival_of_the_andals.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the days of the <a href=\"/index.php/Hundred_Kingdoms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hundred Kingdoms\">Hundred Kingdoms</a>, the mouth of the <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Rush\" title=\"Blackwater Rush\">Blackwater Rush</a> was claimed by the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">Darklyns</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Massey\" title=\"House Massey\">Masseys</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Stonedance\" title=\"Stonedance\">Stonedance</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/River_kings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"River kings\">river kings</a> of Houses <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mudd\" title=\"House Mudd\">Mudd</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Fisher\" title=\"House Fisher\">Fisher</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bracken\" title=\"House Bracken\">Bracken</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackwood\" title=\"House Blackwood\">Blackwood</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hook\" title=\"House Hook\">Hook</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The river's mouth was successfully claimed by King <a href=\"/index.php/Benedict_II_Justman\" title=\"Benedict II Justman\">Benedict II Justman</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Prior to <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>, the Blackwater was disputed by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hoare\" title=\"House Hoare\">House Hoare</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_the_Isles_and_the_Rivers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of the Isles and the Rivers\">Kings of the Isles and the Rivers</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_Kings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Storm Kings\">Storm Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Houses <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">Velaryon</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Celtigar\" title=\"House Celtigar\">Celtigar</a>, all families of <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyrian</a> origin, settled at <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Claw_Isle\" title=\"Claw Isle\">Claw Isle</a>, respectively.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Crownlands_men&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Felicia_Cano_Scavengers_of_King%27s_Landing.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1a/Felicia_Cano_Scavengers_of_King%27s_Landing.JPG/350px-Felicia_Cano_Scavengers_of_King%27s_Landing.JPG\" width=\"350\" height=\"232\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1a/Felicia_Cano_Scavengers_of_King%27s_Landing.JPG/525px-Felicia_Cano_Scavengers_of_King%27s_Landing.JPG 1.5x, /images/1/1a/Felicia_Cano_Scavengers_of_King%27s_Landing.JPG 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Felicia_Cano_Scavengers_of_King%27s_Landing.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Scavengers of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, by Felicia Cano © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, the bustling capital of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>, is located in the <a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">crownlands</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> is found in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Hall_(Red_Keep)\" title=\"Great Hall (Red Keep)\">throne room</a> of the city's <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a> is another prominent town on the shores of <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Bay\" title=\"Blackwater Bay\">Blackwater Bay</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> \"Waters\" is a common <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> name around the bay.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a> is the predominant religion of the province, with the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a> seated at the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a> in King's Landing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Crackclaw_Point\" title=\"Crackclaw Point\">Crackclaw Point</a> is a rugged peninsula in the northern crownlands. Descending from the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> the <a href=\"/index.php/Crackclaws\" title=\"Crackclaws\">Crackclaws</a> are considered half wild by some.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood\" title=\"Kingswood\">kingswood</a> is divided between the southern crownlands and the northern <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlaw\">Outlaws</a> have been known to hide in the forested land.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Crownlands_men&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Now <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">the city</a> covered the shore as far as Catelyn could see; manses and arbors and granaries, brick storehouses and timbered inns and merchant's stalls, taverns and <a href=\"/index.php/Lichyard\" title=\"Lichyard\">graveyards</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Brothel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brothel\">brothels</a>, all piled one on another. She could hear the clamor of the <a href=\"/index.php/Fish_market\" title=\"Fish market\">fish market</a> even at this distance. Between the buildings were broad roads lined with trees, wandering crookback streets, and alleys so narrow that two men could not walk abreast.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>We're all good <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">dragon men</a>, up <a href=\"/index.php/Crackclaw_Point\" title=\"Crackclaw Point\">Crackclaw</a> way.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Dick_Crabb\" title=\"Dick Crabb\">Dick Crabb</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> is a pit of <a href=\"/index.php/Snake\" title=\"Snake\">snakes</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"refe